rior</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/19/02 8:43:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4446.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   proc's mandatory for aggro?</span><hr size=1> Basically, I'm curious to know if proc's are <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>that</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> essential to aggro.  I have been doing a bit of reading and asking some questions about different things pertaining to weapons.  I have decided that I am going to buy a Swiftblade of Zek for my primary hand and The Horn of Hsagra for my off hand.  I will also be using a Sib beserker cloak (I know that the general consensus is CoF, but the price difference killed me) for haste. <br>
<br>
Is there going to be a massive loss in aggro control compared to the Wavecrasher/Snowchipper combo that I currently use?  I'll be using faster and stronger weapons, as well as adding 27% haste.  What do you all think? <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=2372"> Thor Lost Myrmidon</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
