</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=roenae>Roenae</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 107<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/19/02 12:39:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4446.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: proc's mandatory for aggro?</span><hr size=1> Well, the Windblade has a spectacular damage/delay, im not surprised that you can hold agro with it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Oh, and did anyone else notice that its a DIRECT copy of Gimli's axe from the lord of the rings movies?<br>
<br>
Cheap bastards couldn't even design their own weapons =/ <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.warlocksdomain.com/.sig/Roenae_sig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--> <br>
<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=335804">www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=335804</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=raunstoncutter>RaunStoncutter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 236<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/19/02 12:46:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4446.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.liquid2k.com/raunstonecutter/bunnyhop.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: proc's mandatory for aggro?</span><hr size=1> Procs aren't necessairy, I belive someone said that you could keep agro with 2 rusty daggers if need be.<br>
<br>
The prefernce is to get the best weapons you can.  I can't comment on the WC as an agro weapon, but I will site this own personal example of stupidity.<br>
<br>
My guild was killing servitor for fun one night, and our MT had a WC/Red Epic.  I had a Fleshgrinder and Frostbringer.  At one point, I got agro so bad off him, that even taunting wouldn't work, and I of course died.  This happened a 2ed time as well.  I'm not sure how he faired with the other classes.<br>
<br>
This only really illustrates that the FG/FB procing/DPS set up can get some good pop agro, and slowly build it up (hence why he couldn't immedately pull agro off me).<br>
<br>
I personally wouldn't use a WC because it's still a 9/19, even with an extremely nice proc.  I have found that sticking with good DPS weapons helps to maintain agro better for me.  It may not work for you, or you may disagree, but it works for me. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=31658">Raun Stonecutter</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.swordoffate.com">&lt;Sword of Fate&gt;</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=124485">Deterious</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.swordoffate.com">&lt;Sword of Fate&gt;</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=haass>Haass</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 672<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/19/02 3:36:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4446.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: proc's mandatory for aggro?</span><hr size=1> Well, the answer to the question relies heavily on who you're keeping aggro from.<br>
<br>
Can you reasonably keep aggro against your monks and rogues without them spending half the fight with autoattack off?  Then you're fine.  If you can't, then you might need something exta.<br>
<br>
I held aggro pretty well with 2 non proccing weapons when my monk buddy was a few levels below me.  Once he hit 60 and picked up 15/19 and 15/18 weapons, and 41 haste, I needed to get ambidex and I switched to dual fleshgrinders to bring up my DPS enough to where my taunt button could hold aggro.  It works for me.  Do I need to rely on some gimp weapon ratio to do it?  Nah.  If his DPS goes up any more, I might tho.<br>
<br>
It all depends on who you're trying to hold aggro from...if in your situation you can do that, then don't worry about it. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=48986">Marshall Haass Wolvesbane</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=71943">Venerable Cagna Soulshaker</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <br>
<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rani>rani</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 87<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/19/02 6:40:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4446.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: proc's mandatory for aggro?</span><hr size=1> As the poster above said, depends who you are with..<br>
<br>
I use BoC+Primal, and I have to hit taunt ALOT when I group with a 65 monk in guild with Caens Bo Staff(emp 2hb).<br>
<br>
Same goes for when I group with high AA Goldenrod'ed paladins, I usually just say fuckit and let them tank <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
So the problem is if you are grouped with someone whose weapons inherently carry more agro. Sure you can taunt the mob on you for brief periods of time, but because of the way taunt works currently(successfull taunt=Hatelist top+1) after a few swings they will out-agro you again.<br>
<br>
Sooo.. either you need to <br>
<br>
A) Always have better weapons than those you group with, from a pure damage and delay perspective(which in some cases is impossible, you wont be out taunting a Caen 2hander for instance, and Goldenrod is pretty tough to beat too).<br>
<br>
or<br>
<br>
B) Rely on procs (which is what most warriors in the endgame currently is forced to).<br>
<br>
or<br>
<br>
C)  Ask the people you group with to switch to worse weaponry if you cant keep agro. Of course this isnt really an option, they will probably rather replace you, than bag their uberweapon01 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thorilan>thorilan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 288<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/19/02 10:51:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4446.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: proc's mandatory for aggro?</span><hr size=1> lots of factors to look at like <br>
<br>
are you defensive and trying to hold agro against monks rogues wizards and mages .are you in an xp or grind group?<br>
and which proc is right for you if you choose one. personaly instead of SBoZ i would go with a fleshgrinder because its just a little bit better ratio and has a proc. even if its only a dd proc. it still procs really easy. <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=trakceles>trakceles </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/19/02 11:44:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4446.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.marentes.com/bugsmedia/animations/dancing.gif width=58 height=125 ></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: proc's mandatory for aggro?</span><hr size=1> tooo many factors.<br>
<br>
Who you keeping aggro form?<br>
Are you defensive?<br>
What are you fighting? <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.theshadoworder.com"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://web.ecomplanet.com/MCMA9683/ServerContent/MyCustomImages/MCMA9683CustomImage0039127.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:Monotype Corsiva;font-size:x-small;"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=221293">Who cares?</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=northerner>Northerner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/20/02 1:18:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4446.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.shaw.ca/sjgardner/Images/celeris2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: proc's mandatory for aggro?</span><hr size=1> As already said it is all about whom you are trying to keep aggro off of.  <br>
<br>
As a moderately equipped Deceiver I can stay below a Windblade tank in aggro with a small amount of effort and we will be fine in an exp group.  Heck, I can stay below a 61 Warrior with a pair of fleshgrinders too if I need to but I might eat some dps loss to do so.<br>
<br>
In a raid that same tank is in deep, trying to stay above not just me but everyone else as well.  Frankly, that isn't happening without a great two-hander (BBB comes to mind), an EB-proccing mainhand or equivalent or burning AE-taunt/snare glands unless you give that tank some solo-time.  This is worse in a Defensive situation of course, as relying on damage there is simply not an option.<br>
<br>
I do not know any raid tanks that do not rely on some form of proc/clicky for aggro in the short and nasty PoP fights, although that does not mean it cannot be done.  Prox aggro, guildmember discipline and other means can be used to great effect. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:RED;"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=78504">Celeris Tujimson</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Deceiver of The Nameless<br>
</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:CYAN;font-size:x-small;">Success is the ability to go from one failure to another with no loss of enthusiasm.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Sir Winston Churchill</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gedes>Gedes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/20/02 9:56:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4446.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: proc's mandatory for aggro?</span><hr size=1> Ok, well I am not guilded at the moment, so I am exp'ing in pickup groups 99% of the time.  Sadly, the people I'll be trying to hold aggro from will vary greatly from one day to the next.  Usually I am not fighting with defensive on, and if I have to hit defensive (usually if things go wrong and the cleric is Lom), I am not too upset if the mob starts smacking the paladin hehe<br>
<br>
My main concern is just your standard exp group.  Currently with my snowchipper and my WC, I lose exp to others a little too easily.  Now that is dependant on who I am grouped with, some monks and rogues keep aggro on me with no difficulty at all, others take it and then yell &quot;taunt&quot;.  I figured by adding 27% haste and increasing the DPS (and speed) of the weapons I have, it would increase my ability to hold aggro.<br>
<br>
On a slightly different note, I worry that if I stick with procs to hold aggro, then VI reworks taunt to be useful, then I will have shafted myself out of a better dmg/dly ration or better stats/hit points. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=2372"> Thor Lost Myrmidon</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
